//   references        : list of short pointers (notes-mode only)
//
// Threaded example, used every day:
//   E. coli K-12 MG1655 grown in LB to OD600 = 0.5, then split:
//     - 3 control cultures (no drug)
//     - 3 treated cultures (1 μg/mL ampicillin, ~¼ MIC)
//   Harvest 30 min after treatment. Extract RNA. RNA-seq. ~4,000 protein-
//   coding genes × 6 samples counts matrix.
//
//   Marker genes referenced throughout:
//     ampC (β-lactamase)         — strongly induced by β-lactam stress
//     recA (SOS response)        — induced when DNA damage rises
//     acrA (efflux pump)         — induced, exports the drug
//     rpoD (housekeeping σ⁷⁰)    — stable across conditions
//     gapA (glycolysis enzyme)   — stable across conditions
//
//   Stable worked numbers across the week (ampC counts after CPM normalisation):
//     Control:  12, 15, 11    (mean  ≈ 12.67, SD ≈ 2.08)
//     Treated: 145, 178, 162  (mean ≈ 161.67, SD ≈ 16.50)
//   These appear on Day 1 (data shape), Day 2 (t-test by hand), Day 3
//   (volcano plot, PCA), Day 4 (regression on the same gene), Day 5 (foundation
//   model embedding of the whole expression profile).

